args: Time to hit the road and RIDE, baby!
Huh?! What's the haps over that way?!
Eeeee! I'm your biggest fan!\nPlease take this homemade chocolate!
Thank you. I will treasure it always.
Whoa! Look at that turkey go!
I'm sorry, what did you call me?

Every awesome guy is Slick to me!
Anyway, enough gum-flappin' here—
what's up with gettin' all those
toadies to bring ya chocolate?
I think you misunderstand the situation.\nThose were Valentine's presents.

Oh, riiight! That's when everyone hands
out presents to honor strong cats, yeah?
I bet ya knocked all them turkeys out cold
without breakin' a sweat!
You seem terribly misinformed\non what Valentine's is.
Those were not challengers, but fans—\nand they were bringing me presents\nto thank me for my performance.
You don't say? Well, hot potato!\nThat's bad with a capital B!
So whadda I gotta do to be all strong\nand get appreciation gifts like you?

That is a multi-faceted question for certain.
For my part, I merely work every day to
better myself as a conductor; the gifts
are an unintended consequence.
Aces, my man! I get it now!

You showed 'em how hardcore you are
by conducting, and they responded by
tearin' open their wallets and makin'
it rain presents!
So if I just show 'em what an ace I am\non my chariot, they'll do the same to me!
Er, no. I don't think... Oh dear.
Outta the way, turkeys! One stone-cold\nbiker, comin' through! VROOOOM!
Make way for the king'a Valentine's!\nThe pope'a presents! The god'a goodies!
Well, that was a rather nasty experience.
NO RUNNING OR BIKING IN THE\nCORRIDORS, YOU HOOLIGAN!
If ya wanna give me any gifts,\nnow's the time, turkeys!
And so, Yuya rode around the Halidom like a\ndragon on fire in an effort to gain attention.\nBut in the end...
Well, this is a square deal for sure...\nI got no gifts! Not even one!
Didn't any of those turkeys get how bad\nI was? Didn't they see the chariot? *sniff*\nAw man, here come the waterworks...
'Tis I, the avatar of loveliness!\nZardin the magnificent!
Can't believe this cat's lookin' in a\nmirror while he talks to me. Wild!

I witnessed you charging through the halls
of the castle showing your beauty to all.
And beautiful you were—though not quite
at my level, naturally.
You sayin' I'm super cool? 'Cause I is!
I suppose that is also an apt description.\nStill, if you allow me to aid you, I can take\nyour unrefined beauty to the next level.
This Ultra Cleansing Oil is the answer\nyou weren't even aware you were\nsearching for!
No idea what that is, but I'm up for\nanything that sounds super wild!

It IS super wild, my strange new friend!
Just rub it into your face thoroughly,
and you will be shining like a newly
born star before you know it.
I would never jape about an appearance!\nYou may consider this a gift from your\nancestors in beauty. Use it well!
Right on! I'm gonna turn bright as the sun\nand THEN show everyone how hardcore\nI am. Let's get rollin', baby!
Er, so this is the village where fiends\nhave been prowling around at night?\nI...I guess I'm r-ready?
This is no time for being scared.\nWe've got a patrol to finish.
What IS that strange light...?\nAnd why is it coming right for us?!
Yo! Nice job with the patrol, Slicks!
You dig my chariot? Yeah, it's real bright.
I covered it in some ultra somethin'-or-\nother goo, and now it's DAZZLIN'!
A-are you talking about Zardin's oil?\nThe one he's always haranguing\npeople to use?
Yeah, I think that's actually supposed\nto go on your FACE.
That goo made my chariot look like\na full-blown star or somethin'.\nCan you DIG it, Slicks?!
Now we're gonna ride like the wind—\nI mean, like the LIGHT!

And so, Yuya raced off into the night, his original
goal long-since forgotten. But the fiends who had
been causing trouble for the village feared his
newfound glow, so his presence kept them away.

As thanks for his good deed, the villagers
presented him with some sweet potatoes.
Thus ends the tale of how Yuya took Valentine's
to task like a stone-cold boss.
